o.value: ISO 639-5 Codes for the Representation of Names of Languages â€“ Part 5: Alpha-3 Code for Language Families and Groups

This part of ISO 639 provides a code consisting of language code elements comprising three-letter language identifiers for the representation of names of living and extinct language families and groups. Languages designed exclusively for machine use, such as computer-programming languages, are not to be included in this code.
